Performance Requirements
NFR-1: Response Time
  Description: The system shall respond to user actions within acceptable time limits
  Criteria:
Page load time: ≤ 2 seconds
Login authentication: ≤ 1 second
Product listing: ≤ 2 seconds
Cart operations (add/remove/update): ≤ 1 second
Order submission: ≤ 3 seconds
Priority: High
Rationale: Users expect fast interaction when browsing and purchasing products
Security Requirements
NFR-2: Authentication Security
Description: The system shall securely authenticate users
Criteria:
Users must log in with username and password
Only authenticated users can access the system
Different roles (consumer/admin) must have different access rights
Priority: High
Rationale: Prevent unauthorized access to the system
NFR-3: Data Protection
Description: The system shall protect user data
Criteria:
Passwords must be stored securely (hashed)
Users can access only their own data
Sensitive data must not be exposed
Priority: Critical
Rationale: Ensure confidentiality of user information
Reliability Requirements
NFR-4: System Reliability
Description: The system shall function correctly under normal conditions
Criteria:
No data loss during normal operations
Errors should not crash the application
System must handle invalid inputs gracefully
Priority: High
Rationale: Ensure a stable user experience
Data Integrity Requirements
NFR-5: Data Consistency
Description: The system shall maintain consistent data
Criteria:
Stock must update correctly after order submission
No negative stock values allowed
Orders must reflect correct products and quantities
Priority: High
Rationale: Prevent incorrect system behavior
Scalability Requirements
NFR-6: Concurrent Users
Description: The system shall support multiple users simultaneously
Criteria:
Support at least 20–50 concurrent users
No major performance degradation under load
Priority: Medium
Rationale: Ensure usability for multiple users
Availability Requirements
NFR-7: System Availability
Description: The system shall be available at all times
Criteria:
Application should be accessible 24/7
Downtime should be minimal
Priority: High
Rationale: Users need constant access to the application
